<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-570-582  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 570 582.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  August 28 1989 v6 n34 p13(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>VMSmail linked to Macs, PCs, OS/2 platforms. (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ballou, Melinda-Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   CC:Mail Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   VMS (Operating system) (computer programs)Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (computer programs)VMSlink (computer network software) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Electronic Mail SystemsSoftware MigrationConnectivityProduct IntroductionOS-2MS-DOS.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>VMSmail Linked To Macs, PCs, OS/2 PlatformsandM;PALO ALTO, Calif.andP;  -- A direct interface from Macintosh, DOS and OS/2platforms to VMSmail will be available at the end of next month from cc:Mail,company officials said.andM;Called VMSlink, the product is currently in beta test and was demonstrated atthe MacWorld exhibition in Boston earlier this month.andM;VMSlink will not initially support DEC's Message Router/Mailbus, but theofficials said another product, called All-in-1 link, will be availablebefore the end of the year to support Message Router/Mailbus.andM;cc:Mail has also been shipping a local area network package for the Macintoshsince June, providing Macintoshes with connectivity to DOS or OS/2-based PCs,including server-to-server, LAN-to-LAN, Profs, EasyLink, Telemail and MHSconnections.andM;Major features of the local area network package include transparent filetransfer and compound document delivery between platforms, automaticconversion among popular grapics displays (CGA, EGA, VGA and Hercules) anddistributed mail server software.andM;Other main features of the package include encrypted, compressed messages anduser directory files; a user directory capacity of 65,000 names; bulletinboards; file archiving; access to mailing lists; and system accessindependent of network node or platform, the officials said.andM;Fax/E-Mail IntegrationandM;Futures releases of the LAN product will integrate facsimile capabilitieswith electronic mail, as well as admiistration and installation facilities,according to the officials.andM;Prices for VMSlink range from $1,495 to $2,495.andM;The LAN package for the Macintosh is priced at $495.andM;For more information, cc:Mail Inc. can be contacted at 385 Sherman Ave., PaloAlto, CA 94306, (415) 321-0458.andO;</TEXT></DOC>